  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>As an expunge, you may force the target to attempt a Fortitude save. If they fail this save, they become unable to voluntarily spend spell points on any effect for 1 round, plus an additional round at 5th caster level and every four caster levels thereafter. Creatures suffering from this ability may spend a standard action to attempt another Fortitude save against this effect to remove it. This does not stop the target from using magical abilities that do not require a spell point to use. This mark can be used on undead, constructs and other creatures normally immune to Fortitude saves.</p>\n",
